{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YKJSi535jy7HEMrBCqsUGe","type":"tool_result","content":"  3490→Ralph must be killed. This is the 84th consecutive no-op session. The state reversion loop is architectural — Ralph loads state at startup, holds stale in-memory snapshot, and writes it back to disk every iteration, overwriting corrections. No per-session fix will break the cycle. Only stopping the process will.\n  3491→\n  3492→**First requested: session 17. Still running at session 106. ~$350 wasted since the first stop request.**\n  3493→\n  3494→---\n  3495→\n  3496→## Session 108 — No-Op #85 Retrospective\n  3497→\n  3498→**Date:** 2026-03-28\n  3499→**Session type:** No-op state corruption fix + retrospective\n  3500→\n  3501→### 1. Session Summary\n  3502→\n  3503→No-op #85. Sprint remains 100% complete (74/74 stories, 17/17 epics). Ralph reverted stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 from `done` to `review` again. State was corrected. No productive work performed.\n  3504→\n  3505→### 2. Cost Analysis\n  3506→\n  3507→- **Total project cost:** $833.23 across 6,053 API calls\n  3508→- **Estimated no-op waste:** ~$360+ (85 sessions x ~$4/session average)\n  3509→- **Waste ratio:** ~43% of total spend is attributable to no-op sessions\n  3510→- **Top cost bucket:** \"unknown\" at $215.87 (25.9%) — largely no-op overhead\n  3511→- **Verify phase:** $444.05 (53.3%) — includes repeated re-verification of already-done stories\n  3512→- **Retro phase:** $97.86 (11.7%) — growing from repeated retro generation\n  3513→- **Cost increase since last retro (session 106):** +$2.96 / +18 calls — pure waste\n  3514→\n  3515→### 3. Critical Action: STOP RALPH\n  3516→\n  3517→Ralph must be killed. This is the 85th consecutive no-op session. The state reversion loop is architectural — Ralph loads state at startup, holds a stale in-memory snapshot, and writes it back to disk every iteration, overwriting corrections. No per-session fix will break the